gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 105, Raptors 96
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics defeated the Raptors, 105-96. Jrue Holiday (22 points, six rebounds, seven assists, four 3PM) and Jayson Tatum (19 points, 14 rebounds, six assists) combined for 41 points for the Celtics in the victory, while RJ Barrett tallied 24 points, nine rebounds and four assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Celtics have won back-to-back games as they improve to 31-9 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 15-25.
